Yes, you can draw a string on a canvas in vertical mode by using the rotate method of the canvas context to rotate the text. For example, you can rotate the context by 90 degrees (œÄ/2 radians) and then draw the text. Here's a simple example:

var canvas = document.getElementById('canvas');
var ctx = canvas.getContext('2d');
ctx.font = '20px Arial';
ctx.save();
ctx.translate(50, 100); // Move the context to the desired position
ctx.rotate(-Math.PI / 2); // Rotate the context 90 degrees counterclockwise
ctx.fillText('Vertical Text', 0, 0);
ctx.restore();
This code will draw the text "Vertical Text" vertically on the canvas.

