Answer RAG:
You can use the nsIXULStore interface to store simple key-value pairs, including integers, with more precision than seconds. This interface is designed for storing small amounts of data and is simpler than using preferences. You can access it via JavaScript in your Firefox extension or application. Here's a quick example:

let xulStore = Components.classes["@mozilla.org/xul/xulstore;1"]
                         .getService(Components.interfaces.nsIXULStore);
xulStore.setValue("your-namespace", "your-key", "your-timestamp-value");
let timestamp = xulStore.getValue("your-namespace", "your-key");
This allows you to store and retrieve your timestamp with the desired precision without using preferences.

